+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0199Mrx9oi8CdTSUGfnryYAv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, there's a subtlety here. The gap constraint says \"Events in the same room must have at least `options.gap` minutes between them (end of one event to start of the next).\" So the gap is between end and start, not symmetric. Let me fix the overlap check:\n\n- Event A ends at `a.endTime`, next event starts at `start` → need `a.endTime + gap <= start`\n- Our event ends at `end`, next event A starts at `a.startTime` → need `end + gap <= a.startTime`\n\nThat's what I have. But let me also think about the case where gap is 0. The condition `end + 0 <= a.startTime || a.endTime + 0 <= start` means events can be exactly adjacent. That seems correct.\n\nNow let me also think about the \"Try before first event\" case more carefully. If `earliest = 540` and first event starts at `540`, we'd need `end + gap <= 540`, so only works if `earliest + duration + gap <= 540`. With `earliest = 540`, that requires `duration + gap <= 0`, which won't work. So our event would need to go after the first event. The candidate `sorted[0].endTime + gap` handles that.\n\nLet me also consider an edge case: what if `earliest` falls in the middle of an existing event? The candidate `earliest` would fail the overlap check, and then `sorted[i].endTime + gap` candidates would be tried. That should work.\n\nLet me build and lint again."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1512,"cache_read_input_tokens":36662,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1512},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e432ed4-eb72-4841-831f-2bed515084dd","uuid":"f65e8971-66f1-4c23-9c9d-e100fe3f2d45"}
